Among Muslim women, 65% approve of abortion, although seven in ten Serbian women approve. Abortion thus largely sees no difference in approval – it is largely accepted in Montenegro. According to data from the Montenegrin statistics office, in five years (2014-2018) a total of 38 273 gynecological procedures were performed, of which 21 642 abortions. The total number of abortions in 2014 was 6782. In 2015, the figure was 7182. In 2016, 7,692 abortions were performed (a significant decrease). In 2017, the number of abortions reached 8,172 (a considerable increase) and in 2018 the number of performed abortions was 5,769.

How many abortions

The investigation suggests the number of abortions increased considerably from 2017 to 2018. According to the Eurostat report, “trends 2019”, the annual number of abortions in Montenegro has increased from 5727 in 2017 to 5769 in 2018. For another comparison with the figure, it should be pointed out that in 2018 120 deaths were recorded and registered in Montenegro.
